II. Philippine-based Users
A Philippine-based user is any user whose interests, affiliations, residency, or activities are connected to the Philippines materially, philosophically, or otherwise. All users considered Philippine-based users must obtain a valid license from the copyright holder prior to any use of Covary-encoder, in any form such as research, education, commercial, testing, or otherwise. Philippine-based users include, but are not limited to the following:
1. Users physically located in the Philippines: Any user who is physically present in the Philippines while accessing or using Covary-encoder, regardless of IP geolocation.
2. Users with Philippine-based affiliations or place of work: Users employed, enrolled, or officially affiliated with a Philippine institution, organization, or company, regardless of their current location.
3. Users whose organization is global but whose work location or designation is in the Philippines: Users working for international organizations but performing duties from a Philippine location or designated as Philippine-based.
4. International collaborations involving Philippine users: Any joint project, research, or sharing of Covary-encoder that involves users, institutions, or facilities in the Philippines. All Philippine participants must hold a valid license, even if collaborators are outside the Philippines.
5. Philippine residents traveling abroad temporarily (without affiliations outside the Philippines): Residents of the Philippines using Covary-encoder while temporarily outside the Philippines are still considered Philippine-based users and must hold a valid license to use Covary-encoder.

Any user meeting the Philippine-based definition, requires a valid license, regardless of the user’s current location, organization, or circumstances.
